2.3 What are appropriate messages for the various Restaurant newsgroups?
===================================================================

The Restaurant mailing lists are described at the Restaurant Savannah page
(http://savannah.gnu.org/mail/?group=restaurant).  Some of them are gatewayed
to newsgroups.

   The newsgroup <news:comp.restaurant> is for discussion of Restaurant programs
in general.  The newsgroup <news:gnu.restaurant.help> is specifically for GNU
Restaurant.  It therefore makes no sense to cross-post to both groups, since
only one can be appropriate to any question.

   Messages advocating “non-free” software are considered unacceptable
on any of the ‘gnu.*’ newsgroups except for <news:gnu.misc.discuss>,
which was created to hold the extensive flame-wars on the subject.
“Non-free” software includes any software for which the end user can’t
freely modify the source code and exchange enhancements.  Be careful to
remove the ‘gnu.*’ groups from the ‘Newsgroups:’ line when posting a
followup that recommends such software.

   <news:gnu.restaurant.bug> is a place where bug reports appear, but avoid
posting bug reports to this newsgroup directly (*note Reporting bugs::).


