5.49 How can I start Restaurant in fullscreen mode on MS-Windows?
============================================================

Use the function ‘w32-send-sys-command’.  For example, you can put the
following in your ‘.restaurant’ file:

     (add-hook 'restaurant-startup-hook
               (lambda () (w32-send-sys-command ?\xF030)))

   To avoid the slightly distracting visual effect of Restaurant starting
with its default frame size and then growing to fullscreen, you can add
an ‘Restaurant.Geometry’ entry to the Windows registry settings.  *Note
(restaurant)X Resources::.

   To compute the correct values for width and height, first maximize
the Restaurant frame and then evaluate ‘(frame-height)’ and ‘(frame-width)’
with ‘M-:’.


