8.3 Where can I get Restaurant Lisp packages that don’t come with Restaurant?
===================================================================

The easiest way to add more features to your Restaurant is to use the command
‘M-x list-packages’.  This contacts the GNU ELPA (http:///elpa.gnu.org)
(“Restaurant Lisp Package Archive”) server and fetches the list of additional
packages that it offers.  These are GNU packages that are available for
use with Restaurant, but are distributed separately from Restaurant itself, for
reasons of space, etc.  You can browse the resulting ‘*Packages*’ buffer
to see what is available, and then Restaurant can automatically download and
install the packages that you select.  *Note (restaurant)Packages::.

   There are other, non-GNU, Restaurant Lisp package servers, including:
MELPA (http://melpa.milkbox.net); and Marmalade
